  "title": "Senior Executive Assistant, Community Operations, RHSO(9448)",
  "description": "<p>Provide administrative support to the regional community operations in leading a healthy lifestyle within the community.</p><p><u><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Data entry, scheduling appointments and billing of services</li><li>Staff on-boarding / off-boarding </li><li>Receive and respond to all enquiries via phone call</li><li>Inventory management of consumables and equipment</li><li>Ensure data entry and billing activities are promptly and accurately captured in the respective database and/or systems within the stipulated timeline</li><li>Ensure staff receives the appropriate access and equipment on the first day of work</li><li>Ensure all relevant access and equipment are reclaimed / terminated on staff’s last day of work</li><li>Ensure all enquiries are promptly and professionally handled within the stipulated timeline</li><li>Ensure all relevant consumables and inventory are adequate to meet operational needs</li><li>Any other duties assigned</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in any discipline</li><li>At least 2 years of working experience<br /></li><li>Self-motivated and strong team player<br /></li><li>Meticulous and strong organizational skills<br /></li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office (PowerPoint, Word and Excel)</li><li>Effective written and verbal communication skill<br /></li><li>Must be able to commit on weekends and public holidays</li></ul>",
